Maybe you're a little bit irritated.
可能你有点烦躁。

227
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:08,160
Oh, for Pete's sake, Marco.
哦，看在彼得的份上，马可。

228
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:09,160
Stop giving me examples.
别再给我举例子了。

229
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:11,000
I'm just, I'm done hearing them.
我真是听够了。

230
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,000
Yeah.
是啊。

231
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,680
So there are a lot of other ways to say this, right?
还有很多其他说法，对吧？

232
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,680
Yeah.
对。

233
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:16,000
So you could say for goodness sake.
所以你可以说“看在老天的份上”。

234
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:19,040
For goodness sake or oh, for heaven's sake.
看在老天的份上，或者哦，看在老天的份上。

235
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,440
For heaven's sake.
看在老天的份上。

236
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,440
And finally, for God's sake.
最后，看在上帝的份上。

237
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,440
Right.
对。

238
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:26,560
But this one you have to be careful because some people who are religious might be offended
但这个要小心，因为有些信教的人可能会被冒犯

239
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:27,560
if you use it.
如果你用的话。

240
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:31,240
So if that's the case, then you would just rather go with Pete's sake, heaven's sake
所以如果是那样，你最好用“Pete's sake”或“heaven's sake”。

241
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:33,200
or goodness sake.
看在老天的份上。

242
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,200
Okay.
好的。

243
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,200
For goodness sake.
看在老天的份上。

244
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:38,320
It's a very common phrase and as you say, it's for when you're a little bit irritated.
这是一个很常见的短语，正如你所说，用于你有点烦躁的时候。

245
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,880
It's like oh, for goodness sake.
就像“哦，看在老天的份上”。

246
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:40,880
Stop complaining.
别抱怨了。

247
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:41,880
Exactly.
没错。

248
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:42,880
Right?
对吧？

249
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:43,880
Okay.
好的。

250
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:45,120
